Music icon Caiphus Semenya turns 80. A massive celebration is expected to take place at the Johannesburg's Market Theatre this Saturday. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - One of South Africa's greatest musicians Caiphus Semenya will be celebrating his 80th birthday with a concert over the weekend. Caiphus Semenya at 80 Music Extravaganza: Celebrating a Milestone and the Birth of a Legacy, will include performances from Tsepo Tshola, Sipho Hotstix Mabuse and Condry Ziqubu. READ: Chris McGregor’s compositions return home The event will be hosted at The Market Theatre on Saturday, 24 August. The proceeds from the concert will go to Semenya's National Academy of Africa's Performing Arts in Jabulani, Soweto.